Biography

2022

• Played in all 28 matches, posting a 23-5 record with Chloe Tome in the No. 2 flight

• The pairs’ 23 wins was the most in a single-season in program history

• Outscored opponents 1,202-879 on the season

• Her and Tome became the first MSU pair to eclipse 20 wins in a season

• 18 of their 23 victories came courtesy of sweeps

• Swept Tulane in the CCSA tournament on April 29.

• Recorded a win over No. 9 Stanford on April 16

• Is the all-time individual career wins leader with 39

2021

• Played 15 matches as a sophomore, posting a 12-3 record with Chloe Tome in the No. 2 spot

• The pairs’ 12 wins was the most in a single-season in program history

• Won their first eight matches of the season before falling to Central Arkansas in three sets

• Recorded two wins over ranked opponents defeating Arizona (March 3) and LSU (March 23)

2020

• Appeared in all 12 matches as a true freshman, going 4-5 in the No. 3 pair, 0-2 in the second flight and 0-1 at the four spot

• Played nine matches with Rachel Tam

• Went 4-2 against unranked teams with victories against Boise State (Feb. 21), San Francisco (Feb. 22), Florida Memorial (Feb. 28) and UAB (March 6)

Background

• Spent most of her high school career for the Eagles’ No. 1 pair, earning rookie of the year honors in the program’s inaugural season in spring 2017

• Team MVP as a junior on a club that posted an unbeaten record and advanced to the Arizona Division I Final Four

• Top-eight finisher at the Arizona State Pairs Tournament in 2018

• Played setter and right side for the Sandra Day O’Connor High indoor team

Personal

• Born January 30, 2001 in Wichita Falls, Texas

• Daughter of JJ Cook and Lee and Vincent Pagano

• Exercise and movement science major
